arked-by-low-turnout-fraud-claims/28728417.html Ruling Party Dominates Russian Elections Amid Low Turnout, Opposition Claims Strong Moscow Showing]</ref>\n|legislature=[[People's Khural of the Republic of Buryatia|People's Khural]]\n|legislature_ref=<ref name=\"HeadLegis\" />\n|website=http://egov-buryatia.ru/\n|website_ref\n|date=February 2017\n}}\nThe '''Republic of Buryatia''' ({{lang-rus|\u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0301\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0411\u0443\u0440\u044f\u0301\u0442\u0438\u044f|r=Respublika Buryatiya|p=r\u02b2\u026as\u02c8publ\u02b2\u026ak\u0259 b\u028a\u02c8r\u02b2\u00e6t\u02b2\u026aj\u0259}}; {{lang-bua|\u0411\u0443\u0440\u044f\u0430\u0434 \u0423\u043b\u0430\u0441|Buryaad Ulas}}, {{IPA-all|b\u028a\u02c8r\u02b2\u0251\u02d0t \u028a\u02c8l\u0251s|pron}}, {{lang-mn|\u0411\u0443\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0434 \u0423\u043b\u0441|Buriad Uls}}) is a [[federal subjects of Russia|federal subject]] of [[Russia]] (a [[republics of Russia|republic]]), located in [[Siberia]] in [[Asia]]. Formerly part of the [[Siberian Federal District]], it has been a part of the [[Russian Far East]] since 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://publication.pravo.gov.ru/Document/View/0001201811040002?index=0&rangeSize=1|title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0442-\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438|website=publication.pravo.gov.ru|access-date=2018-11-04}}</ref> Its [[capital city|capital]] is the [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]] of [[Ulan-Ude]]. Its area is {{convert|351,300|km2|sp=us}} with a population of 972,021 ([[Russian Census (2010)|2010 Census]]).<ref name=\"2010Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2010Census}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0411\u0430\u0439\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430.jpg|right|thumb|View of [[Lake Baikal]] in Buryatia]]\n[[File:View_of_the_valley_of_the_Uda_near_the_village_of_Khorinsk.jpg|thumb|294x294px|View of the valley of the Uda near the village of Khorinsk.]]\n[[File:Southernburyatia.jpg|right|thumb|300px|Landscape of southern Buryatia.]]\n\nThe republic is located in the south-central region of Siberia along the eastern shore of [[Lake Baikal]].\n*Area: 351,300&nbsp;km\u00b2\n*Borders:\n**Internal: [[Irkutsk Oblast]] (W/NW/N), [[Zabaykalsky Krai]] (NE/E/SE/S), [[Tuva]] (W)\n**International: [[Mongolia]] ([[Bulgan Province]], [[Kh\u00f6vsg\u00f6l Province]] and [[Selenge Province]]) (S/SE)\n**Water: [[Lake Baikal]] (N)\n*Highest point: Mount [[Munku-Sardyk]] (3,491 m)\n<!--\n*''Maximum N->S distance'': no data.\n*''Maximum E->W distance'': no data.\n*''Average elevation'': no data\n-->\n\n===Rivers===\nMajor rivers include:\n*[[Barguzin River]]\n*[[Irkut River]]\n*[[Kitoy River]]\n*[[Oka River (Siberia)|Oka River]]\n*[[Selenga River]]\n*[[Uda River (Republic of Buryatia)|Uda River]]\n*[[Upper Angara River]]\n*[[Vitim River]]\n\n===Lakes===\n[[File:Buryatia02.png|right|thumb|250px|Map of Buryatia.]]\n*[[Lake Baikal]] - Buryatia covers 60% percent of the lake's shoreline.\n*[[Lake Gusinoye]]\n\n===Mountains===\nOver 80% of the republic's territory is located in the mountainous region, including the [[Baikal Mountains]] on the northern shores of [[Lake Baikal]], the [[Ulan-Burgas]] east of the lake and the [[Selenga Highlands]] in the south near the [[Mongolia\u2013Russia border]].\n\n===Natural resources===\nThe republic's natural resources include [[gold]], [[tungsten]], [[zinc]], [[uranium]], and more.\n\n===Climate===\n*Average annual temperature: {{convert|-1.6|C}}\n*Average January temperature: {{convert|-22|C}}\n*Average July temperature: {{convert|+18|C}}\n*Average annual [[precipitation (meteorology)|precipitation]]: {{convert|244|mm|sp=us}}\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n{{Main|Administrative divisions of Buryatia}}\n\