ral_district=[[Far Eastern Federal District|Far Eastern]]\n|economic_region=[[East Siberian economic region|East Siberian]]\n|adm_ctr_type=Capital\n|adm_ctr_name=[[Ulan-Ude]]\n|adm_ctr_ref\n|official_lang_list=[[Buryat language|Buryat]]\n|official_lang_ref=<ref name=\"Languages\">Constitution, Article&nbsp;67</ref>\n|pop_2010census=972021\n|pop_2010census_rank=54th\n|urban_pop_2010census=58.4%\n|rural_pop_2010census=41.6%\n|pop_2010census_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|pop_density\n|pop_density_as_of\n|pop_density_ref\n|pop_latest\n|pop_latest_date\n|pop_latest_ref\n|area_km2=351300\n|area_km2_rank=15th\n|area_km2_ref\n|established_date={{start date and age|1923|5|30|df=y}}\n|established_date_ref\n|license_plates=03\n|ISO=RU-BU\n|gov_as_of=March 2011\n|leader_title=[[Head of the Republic of Buryatia|Head]]\n|leader_title_ref=<ref name=\"HeadLegis\">Constitution, Article&nbsp;5.3</ref>\n|leader_name=[[Alexey Tsydenov]]\n|leader_name_ref=<ref>[https://www.rferl.org/a/russia-local-elections-marked-by-low-turnout-fraud-claims/28728417.html Ruling Party Dominates Russian Elections Amid Low Turnout, Opposition Claims Strong Moscow Showing]</ref>\n|legislature=[[People's Khural of the Republic of Buryatia|People's Khural]]\n|legislature_ref=<ref name=\"HeadLegis\" />\n|website=http://egov-buryatia.ru/\n|website_ref\n|date=February 2017\n}}\nThe '''Republic of Buryatia''' ({{lang-rus|\u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0301\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0411\u0443\u0440\u044f\u0301\u0442\u0438\u044f|r=Respublika Buryatiya|p=r\u02b2\u026as\u02c8publ\u02b2\u026ak\u0259 b\u028a\u02c8r\u02b2\u00e6t\u02b2\u026aj\u0259}}; {{lang-bua|\u0411\u0443\u0440\u044f\u0430\u0434 \u0423\u043b\u0430\u0441|Buryaad Ulas}}, {{IPA-all|b\u028a\u02c8r\u02b2\u0251\u02d0t \u028a\u02c8l\u0251s|pron}}, {{lang-mn|\u0411\u0443\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0434 \u0423\u043b\u0441|Buriad Uls}}) is a [[federal subjects of Russia|federal subject]] of [[Russia]] (a [[republics of Russia|republic]]), located in [[Siberia]] in [[Asia]]. Formerly part of the [[Siberian Federal District]], it has been a part of the [[Russian Far East]] since 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://publication.pravo.gov.ru/Document/View/0001201811040002?index=0&rangeSize=1|title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0442-\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438|website=publication.pravo.gov.ru|access-date=2018-11-04}}</ref> Its [[capital city|capital]] is the [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]] of [[Ulan-Ude]]. Its area is {{convert|351,300|km2|sp=us}} with a population of 972,021 ([[Russian Census (2010)|2010 Census]]).<ref name=\"2010Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2010Census}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0411\u0430\u0439\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430.jpg|right|thumb|View of [[Lake Baikal]] in Buryatia]]\n[[File:View_of_the_valley_of_the_Uda_near_the_village_of_Khorinsk.jpg|thumb|294x294px|View of the valley of the Uda near the village of Khorinsk.]]\n[[File:Southernburyatia.jpg|right|thumb|300px|Landscape of southern Buryatia.]]\n\nThe republic is located in the south-central region of Siberia along the eastern shore of [[Lake Baikal]].\n*Area: 351,300&nbsp;km\u00b2\n*Borders:\n**Internal: [[Irkutsk Oblast]] (W/NW/N), [[Zabaykalsky Krai]] (NE/E/SE/S), [[Tuva]] (W)\n**International: [[Mongolia]] ([[Bulgan Province]], [[Kh\u00f6vsg\u00f6l Province]] and [[Selenge Province]]) (S/SE)\n**Water: [[Lake Baikal]] (N)\n*Highest point: Mount [[Munku-Sardyk]] (3,491 m)\n<!--\n*''Maximum N->S distance'': no data.\n*''Maximum E->W distance'': no data.\n*''Average elevation'': no data\n-->\n\n===Rivers===\nMajor rivers include:\n*[[Barguzin River]]\n*[[Irkut River]]\n*[[Kitoy River]]\n*[[Oka River (Siberia)|Oka River]]\n*[[Selenga River]]\n*[[Uda River (Republic of Buryatia)|Uda River]]\n*[[Upper Angara River]]\n*[[Vitim River]]\n\n===Lakes===\n[[File:Buryatia02.png|right|thumb|250px|Map of Buryatia.]]\n*[[Lake Baikal]] - Buryatia covers 60% percent of the lake's shoreline.\n*[[Lake Gusinoye]]\n\n===Mountains===\nOver 80% of the republic's territory is located in the mountainous region, including the [[Baikal Mountains]] on the northern shores of [[Lake Baikal]], the [[Ulan-Burgas]] east of the lake and the [[Selenga Highlands]] in the south near the [[Mongolia\u2013Russia border]].\n\n===Natural resources===\nThe republic's natural resources include [[gold]], [[tungsten]], [[zinc]], [[uranium]], and more.\n\n===Climate===\n*Average annual temperature: {{convert|-1.6|C}}\n*Average January temperature: {{convert|-22|C}}\n*Average July temperature: {{convert|+18|C}}\n*Average annual [[precipitation (meteorology)|precipitation]]: {{convert|244|mm|sp=us}}\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n{{Main|Administrative divisions of Buryatia}}\n\n==Demographics==\n'''Population''': {{ru-census|p2010=972,021|p2002=981,238|p1989=1,041,119}}\n\n===Settlements===\n{{Largest cities\n| name         = Largest cities\n| country      = Buryatia\n| stat_ref     = 2010 Russian Census\n| list_by_pop  =\n| class        = nav\n| div_name     =\n| div_link     = Administrative divisions of Buryatia{{!}}Administrative division\n| city_1 = Ulan-Ude\n| div_1 = Ulan-Ude{{!}}City of republic significance of Ulan-Ude\n| pop_1 = 404,426\n| img_1 = \u0412\u0438\u0434 \u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043b\u0430\u043d-\u0423\u0434\u044d \u0441 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u041a\u043e\u043c\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0438 - panoramio - Tohuchar (6).jpg\n| city_2 = Severobaykalsk\n| div_2 = Severobaykalsk{{!}}Town of republic significance of Severobaykalsk\n| pop_2 = 24,929\n| img_2 = \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0439\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430.jpg\n| city_3 = Gusinoozyorsk\n| div_3 = Selenginsky District\n| pop_3 = 24,582\n| img_3 = 2014-03-31 12-49-19 \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0438\u043d\u043e\u043e\u0437\u0451\u0440\u0441\u043a.JPG\n| city_4 = Kyakhta\n| div_4 = Kyakhtinsky District\n| pop_4 = 20,041\n| img_4 = Kyahta.s gory.JPG\n| city_5 = Selenginsk\n| div_5 = Kabansky District\n| pop_5 = 14,546\n| city_6 = Zakamensk\n| div_6 = Zakamensky District\n| pop_6 = 11,524\n| city_7 = Onokhoy\n| div_7 = Zaigrayevsky District\n| pop_7 = 10,689\n| city_8 = Taksimo\n| div_8 = Muysky District\n| pop_8 = 9,438\n| city_9 = Bichura, Republic of Buryatia{{!}}Bichura\n| div_9 = Bichursky District\n| pop_9 = 9,145\n| city_10 = Khorinsk\n| div_10 = Khorinsky District\n| pop_10 = 8,138\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! Census date\n! 1926\n! 1939\n! 1959\n! 1970\n! 1979\n! 1989\n! 2002\n! 2010\n|-\n| Total population\n| align=\"right\" | 491,236\n| align=\"right\" | 545,766\n| align=\"right\" | 673,326\n| align=\"right\" | 812,251\n| align=\"right\" | 899,398\n| align=\"right\" | 1,038,252\n| align=\"right\" | 981,238\n| align=\"right\" | 972,021\n|-\n| Average annual population growth\n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | +1.7%\n| align=\"right\" | +1.1%\n| align=\"right\" | +1.5%\n| align=\"right\" style=\"color: red\" | \u22120.4%\n| align=\"right\" style=\"color: red\" | \u22120.1%\n|-\n| Males\n| align=\"right\" | 248,513\n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" |\n| align=\"right\" | 467,984\n| align=\"right\" | \n|-\n| Females\n| align=\"right\" | 242,723\n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" |\n| align=\"right\" | 513,254\n| align=\"right\" | \n|-\n| Females per 1000 males\n| align=\"right\" | 977\n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" | \n| align=\"right\" |\n| align=\"right\" | 1,097\